The paper deals with the issue of security in wireless networks, specifically in cooperative communications where neighbouring nodes act as relays. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes an information self-encrypted approach to protect against untrusted relays, which involves encrypting the original packets of information as secret keys. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with issues related to transmission distance and channel fading, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a combination of techniques to improve security performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
